Name Version ID             Fix Versions Description
---- ------- -------------- ------------ ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
pip  23.2.1  PYSEC-2023-228 23.3         When installing a package from a Mercurial VCS URL  (ie "pip install  hg+...") with pip prior to v23.3, the specified Mercurial revision could  be used to inject arbitrary configuration options to the "hg clone"  call (ie "--config"). Controlling the Mercurial configuration can modify  how and which repository is installed. This vulnerability does not  affect users who aren't installing from Mercurial.
